ngs and trim diy molding installing wainscoting";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/42/b1/ab/42b1abfb929d82af4f8edb111b294d82.png";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcREnTpR7x-6KdZ_KawvhrRWdHbVUhNvJLgQQQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:524;s:6:"height";i:700;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://fr.pinterest.com/pin/602075043914651218/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"fr.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:62:{i:0;s:133:"The chair rail cornice is clearly shown wide-side up the same as the cornice in the entablature or the abacus in the columns capital.";i:1;s:197:"Study of the classical column will answer a lot of questions I found this particular diagram very helpful to understand how the various interior elements come together as a metaphor for the column.";i:2;s:13:"July 21 2016.";i:3;s:138:"Historically chair rails were used to protect plaster when chairs were backed up against the walls to clear space in the middle of a room.";i:4;s:79:"Like many functional inventions this one became more decorative over the years.";i:5;s:104:"It became common to use the rail as a divider strip for paint or wallpaper to create a contrasting look.";i:6;s:103:"A chair rail protects the wall from damage caused by the backs of chairs being pushed against the wall.";i:7;s:165:"It takes the form of a horizontal strip of decorative wood fixed at the same height as the chair backs so that the wood rather than the plasterwork takes the knocks.";i:8;s:78:"Well by the 13rd rule your chair rail would end up at 4 which is WAY too high.";i:9;s:27:"I would go no higher the 3.";i:10;s:30:"32 would be a nice compromise.";i:11;s:99:"The other thing I would do is find other details to tie the chair rail towindow sills cabinets etc.";i:12;s:50:"Let the millwork unify and tie the space together.";i:13;s:23:"Brad g January 19 2014.";i:14;s:255:"In Postwar houses with the same kind of evil rough sanded-plaster walls that we had when I was five a chair rail may protect chairs finish or upholstery from getting shredded but generally a chair rails protection is intended to work the other way around.";i:15;s:141:"Not to protect the chairs but to keep the paint unmarked the plaster un-gouged from the chairs being knocked into or dragged along the walls.";i:16;s:75:"Anonymous wroteChair rail is perhaps the most important moulding in a room.";i:17;s:63:"Not higher than 13 of the ceiling height and lower if possible.";i:18;s:33:"36 hight chair rail is a mistake.";i:19;s:87:"Will you break the chair rail for windows or position the chair rail below the windows.";i:20;s:70:"The height of any paneling that will go above or below the chair rail.";i:21;s:113:"If the chair rail will mark the top edge of wainscoting for instance simply follow the top edge of that material.";i:22;s:143:"The chair rail was originally placed at around a third the height of the wall which put it at the height of your average chair back says Dixon.";i:23;s:46:"Now it depends more on the height of the room.";i:24;s:135:"If the ceiling is really high instead of using the one-third rule you might want to move the chair rail down a bit so it wont look odd.";i:25;s:205:"A chair rail also known as a dado rail is a horizontal piece of trim that usually runs the perimeter of a room approx 36 from the floor but can also be awkwardly placed on a single wall popular in the 90s.";i:26;s:127:"When you have a chair rail it can be hard to figure out whether to use the SAME paint colour on the upper and lower portion of.";i:27;s:97:"However they often get missed since the eye doesnt always travel up or down so they go unnoticed.";i:28;s:63:"Therefore you miss out on the visual interest of the trim work.";i:29;s:83:"Chair rails can be installed at any height and typically they are around eye level.";i:30;s:28:"Rule AndOr Policy Violation.";i:31;s:28:"Received 9 Votes on 8 Posts.";i:32;s:22:"Welcome to the forums.";i:33;s:156:"Some chair rail is installed fat side down but generally i